The application is leads management System. 
This has 4 tables: 
1: profiles (id pk, name, email ck, companyId, password, gender, Address, Phone ck, Role, createdTime, lastEditedTime, isDeleted), 
2: companies (companyId pk, name, email ck, phone, address, Note, createdTime, lastEditedTime, isDeleted), 
3: leads (leadId pk, ownerUserId, assignedUserId, companyId, leadName, phone ck, email ck, status, Location, List<Comment>, Note, createdTime, lastEditedTime, isDeleted), 
4: comments (commentId pk, leadId, companyId, comment text, createdByUserId, status, createdTime, lastEditedTime, isDeleted) . 

Roles (SuperAdmin, Admin, User). 
Status (New, In Conversation, DNP, DND, Not Interested, Out of reach, Wrong details, Rejected, PO etc).

Rules: 
SuperAdmin can create get edit delete any user, admin, company. can get edit delete any lead or comment (not create).
Admin can create get edit delete users, leads, comments from/in their company only. can get all admins from same company.
User can create get edit leads from their company. Can see all comments and add comment to all company leads. can edit/delete own comments. can delete own leads.
id, leadId, CommentId, companyId & OwnerUserId can never be changed after creation
If lead is deleted, all comments get deleted automatically. If Company is deleted, All its users, leads, comments will be deleted. deleteing means marking isDeleted true.
All list pages should have search box (by phone, email), pagination and sort/filter by.
30 day retention policy, if data is isDeleted and last updated 30 days before then gets deleted automatically.

Superadmin sidebar tabs: 
All Companies (Contains list of companies with view, edit and delete buttons), 
All leads(Contains list of leads with view, edit and delete buttons), 
All Comments(Contains list of comments with view, edit and delete buttons), 
All Admins(Contains list of admins with view admin, see comments by user, edit and delete buttons), 
All Users(Contains list of users with view user, see comments by user, edit and delete buttons),

Superadmin Dashboard: 
Create Company, Create Admin, Create User

Admin sidebar tabs: 
All leads (Contains list of leads from his company with view, edit and delete buttons), 
All Comments (Contains list of comments from his company with view, edit and delete buttons), 
All Admins (Contains list of admins from his company with view admin buttons), 
All Users (Contains list of users from his company with view user, see comments by user, edit and delete buttons)
My Leads (Contains list of created leads with view lead, add comment, edit and delete buttons)
My Work (Contains list of assigned leads with view lead, add comment, edit and delete buttons)

Admin Dashboard: 
Create lead, Create User

User sidebar tabs: 
All leads (Contains list of leads from his company with view, add comment and edit buttons), 
My Leads (Contains list of created leads with view lead, add comment, edit and delete buttons)
My Work (Contains list of assigned leads with view lead, add comment and edit buttons. delete button if owned lead)

User Dashboard: 
Create lead

Additional Pages: 
View Company (shows details, see admins, see users, see leads, edit and delete buttons)
View Admin (shows details with comments list, edit and delete buttons for superadmin)
View Lead (shows details with comments list, add comment, edit buttons. delete button for superadmin/admin or users with owned leads)
View User (shows details with comments list, edit and delete buttons)
View Comment (shows details with edit and delete buttons for superadmin/admin or users with owned leads)
Add Comment (lead Id (fetched from lead, cant be changed), status (dropdown, default fetched from lead, changes lead status), commenttext)
Edit Company (name, email ck, phone ck, address, note can be changed)
Edit Admin (name, email ck, phone ck, password, gender, Address can be changed)
Edit Lead (leadName, assignedUserId, email ck, phone ck, status, Location, Notecan be changed)
Edit User (name, password, gender, Address can be changed)
Edit Comment (Comment Text and status can be Changed)

Forms:
Create Company (fields- name, email ck, phone ck, address, note)
Create Admin (fields- name, email ck, companyId (Company Name dropDown), password, gender, Address, Phone ck)
Create User (fields- name, email ck, password, gender, Address, Phone ck)
Create lead (leadName, assignedUserId(Dropdown all admin/user list of company), phone ck, email ck, status *new by default*, Location, Note)
